metadata.name: Vast Difference #3
metadata.description:
This piece explores the dynamic creation of vascular cages around generative geometries. Particles are projected at a generative form, stopping when contact is made with any of the form's faces. A curve is then generated through the particles, based on the order of particle-face collision. Finally, custom tube geometry is extruded along the curve path, determining the final cage mesh. 

Interactivity: 
Panning, rotating, zooming and toggling both the internal form and particle nodes on/off.

Mouse/Trackpad:
drag -> camera rotation
drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
o, n: hide | show particle nodes
i, v: hide | show internal form
p: screen capture

Notes:
Some renders produce noticeable delays, including possible browser alerts/warnings. This is expected behavior.
Please post your favorite 'Vast Difference' screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: Terra Nova #248
metadata.description:
In the year 2250, the first galactic sector stretching a few hundred parsecs were mapped and new worlds identified for the upcoming Terraforming missions. Who knows what one may stumble across wondering across the stars. Some of these planets feel at home, some feel off while the rest seem ALIVE. Part of the Terra universe

This piece consists of 6 layers driven by controlled noise to create different structures without the use of any external textures.

Keypress
‘Q’ Scroll across the environment
‘W’ Scroll across the minted color palette(1000 color variations)
‘E’  / ‘R’ / ‘T’ Toggle layer groups
‘Y’ To rotate the environment
‘O’ for performance details
‘P’ to pause environment rotation
‘S’ to take a high resolution 4096x4096 snapshot(in LIVE view only)

metadata.name: Pixel Heartbeats (animated) #283
metadata.description:
A uniquely generated animated pixel art piece, reminiscent of a beating heart. Based on a 2013 gif piece of mine, the rigidness of the collection's extra large pixels meet organic generative shapes and natural feeling rhythms, resulting in a mood somewhere between the biological and digital worlds.


Each piece features a unique, sharply rendered generative pixel art with a special heartbeat animation rhythm. The collection also includes exciting color and resolution rarity variations.


--


60% Standard red heart colors
35% Unique rare color variants
5% Special "Shiny" animated color


45% low-fi pixel art animations
45% mid-fi pixel art animations
10% hi-fi pixel art animations


Thanks for stopping by and hope you enjoy!

metadata.name: Cave Etchings #159
metadata.description:
Cave Etchings are detailed line drawings generated from unedited AI images of caves, conjoining an AI process with a generative art process. The project is not just an exercise in aesthetics, it is about seeing things the way a computer 'sees'. The original AI cave series focused on how AI Computer Vision can imagine fantastical caves; in cave etchings, the software visualises pixel data as movement, rotating lines according to hue, saturation, and brightness values. The project is inspired by the artwork of Franklin Booth (1874- 1948).
More details here: https://www.plummerfernandez.com/works/cave-etchings/

Instructions:
‘s’ to save
‘h’ to save hi-res version (may look slightly different in viewport as the moiré effect can vary)
‘t’ to download a thank you message
